[56.856511, "o", "xpression. The fastest faithful approach is to \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mrun it in the SCI sandbox via a code block. `(reduce + (range 1 101))` sums integers \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2m1..100 = 5050.\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m• Code:\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(reduce + (range 1 101))\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m└─\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m• Result:\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m5050\r\n    \u001b[2m└─\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 2 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(28409 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(6.3s)\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mThe previous iteration already evaluated `(reduce + (range 1 101))` in the SCI sandbox and \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mreturned 5050. No further work is needed — I can finalize the answer.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[92m┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[92m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mResult\u001b[0m                                                             \u001b[92m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[9"]
